WEBVTT

00:02.336 --> 00:04.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:04.880 --> 00:06.673
Claire:
Can you pop the trunk?

00:06.673 --> 00:09.593
♪♪

00:09.593 --> 00:11.512
Ah!

00:11.512 --> 00:13.764
[ Sighs ]
We made good time.

00:13.764 --> 00:15.307
Thank goodness,
or else we wouldn't have

00:15.307 --> 00:17.726
the full three hours to wait
before our flight.

00:17.726 --> 00:19.394
Great.

00:19.394 --> 00:20.896
♪♪

00:20.896 --> 00:23.106
Alright. Thanks.

00:23.106 --> 00:24.233
[ Trunk shuts ]

00:24.233 --> 00:25.526
Alright.

00:25.526 --> 00:26.777
Oh.

00:28.612 --> 00:29.947
Starbucks is on me.

00:29.947 --> 00:32.324
No kidding.
And I'm getting a cake pop.

00:32.324 --> 00:37.913
♪♪

00:37.913 --> 00:39.540
[ Car door shuts ]

00:39.540 --> 00:42.751
♪♪

00:42.751 --> 00:44.169
Hey, Dr. Reznick.

00:44.169 --> 00:47.714
♪♪

00:47.714 --> 00:49.299
I thought this was
a surgical mission.

00:49.299 --> 00:51.718
Uh, we're bring‐‐
we're bringing some support.

00:51.718 --> 00:54.263
Morgan's gonna help with
patient selection and aftercare.

00:54.263 --> 00:56.890
Oh. That's great.

00:56.890 --> 00:59.685
10 days, huh?
[ Chuckles ]

00:59.685 --> 01:06.900
♪♪

01:06.900 --> 01:08.485
Can't have you
forgetting me.

01:08.485 --> 01:09.695
I'll be back
before you know it.

01:09.695 --> 01:11.530
[ Chuckles ]

01:11.530 --> 01:18.829
♪♪

01:18.829 --> 01:20.539
Tickets, passports,

01:20.539 --> 01:23.917
travel wallet containing
quetzales and American currency.

01:23.917 --> 01:25.168
You've got 'em.

01:25.168 --> 01:27.462
I know,
because I checked.

01:27.462 --> 01:28.589
You alright?

01:28.589 --> 01:30.799
Oh, it's not that heavy.
I got it.

01:30.799 --> 01:33.343
That's not what I meant.

01:33.343 --> 01:35.804
[ Sighs ]
I'm okay.

01:35.804 --> 01:37.723
I think this trip
will be good.

01:37.723 --> 01:39.099
Change things up.

01:39.099 --> 01:42.352
Focus on
helping other people.

01:42.352 --> 01:44.896
For whatever it's worth,
if you ever need to talk,

01:44.896 --> 01:46.481
you can always call me.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.443
I'm not gonna do that.

01:49.443 --> 01:51.069
I know.

01:51.069 --> 01:53.405
We will not have any time
to shop,

01:53.405 --> 01:55.782
but would you or Debbie
like anything from duty‐free?

01:55.782 --> 01:58.160
♪♪

01:58.160 --> 02:01.204
Guatemala is known
for its rum.

02:01.204 --> 02:02.456
We're okay. Thanks.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.376
Okay.

02:06.376 --> 02:09.671
♪♪

02:09.671 --> 02:11.882
[ Car door shuts ]

02:11.882 --> 02:14.301
You're on this trip, too?

02:14.301 --> 02:15.677
Yeah, got inspired
last night,

02:15.677 --> 02:18.764
decided to take some
personal days, go help out.

02:18.764 --> 02:21.141
And you're bringing
a toilet seat?

02:22.225 --> 02:23.560
Spoken like someone

02:23.560 --> 02:26.063
who's never been on
one of these surgical missions.

02:26.063 --> 02:27.814
[ Airplane engine roaring ]

02:27.814 --> 02:34.488
♪♪

02:34.488 --> 02:41.453
♪♪

02:41.453 --> 02:48.085
♪♪

02:48.085 --> 02:50.295
[ Donkeys bray ]

02:50.295 --> 02:58.553
♪♪

02:58.553 --> 03:06.853
♪♪

03:06.853 --> 03:09.356
The airline
will find your bag.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.858
♪♪

03:11.858 --> 03:14.569
We'll get you some clothes
when we get situated.

03:14.569 --> 03:16.655
[ Scoffs ]

03:16.655 --> 03:23.078
♪♪

03:27.749 --> 03:30.502
Would you like some vitamin B12
to help with exhaustion,

03:30.502 --> 03:32.796
or a motion sickness
wristband?

03:32.796 --> 03:34.172
I have an extra.

03:34.172 --> 03:35.674
No, thanks.

03:37.676 --> 03:39.761
I'm glad we're here.

03:41.054 --> 03:42.597
Yes.

03:42.597 --> 03:45.475
After all the loss
this year.

03:45.475 --> 03:48.103
It's just...
such an amazing way

03:48.103 --> 03:51.648
to be reminded what we have
to be grateful for.

03:51.648 --> 03:52.732
Sapo: Careful!

03:52.732 --> 03:54.025
[ Tires screech ]

03:57.529 --> 03:59.197
Let's see.

04:00.782 --> 04:02.242
[ Sheep bleating ]

04:02.242 --> 04:04.619
Pardon me, sir, could you please
move your flock of sheep?

04:04.619 --> 04:07.038
My sheep don't like
to be rushed. Be patient.

04:07.038 --> 04:08.457
These people are our guests.

04:08.457 --> 04:10.292
Well,
I did not invite them.

04:10.292 --> 04:13.795
We're doctors.

04:13.795 --> 04:16.631
It's been a long trip
and we need to get to our hotel.

04:16.631 --> 04:21.178
♪♪

04:21.178 --> 04:23.597
Doctor?

04:23.597 --> 04:27.058
You're a doctor?

04:27.058 --> 04:28.393
Of course I am.

04:30.312 --> 04:32.981
[ Sheep continue bleating ]

04:32.981 --> 04:35.400
It's a fungus.

04:35.400 --> 04:37.068
It's...
It's a fungus!

04:38.528 --> 04:40.489
It's a fungus.

04:46.495 --> 04:49.498
♪♪

04:49.498 --> 04:52.000
[ Insects chirping ]

04:53.293 --> 04:56.505
Thank you!

04:56.505 --> 04:57.756
Whew!

04:57.756 --> 04:59.466
♪♪

04:59.466 --> 05:01.176
Ah.

05:01.176 --> 05:05.764
♪♪

05:05.764 --> 05:06.807
Need help with that?

05:06.807 --> 05:08.558
No, that's a friend thing.

05:08.558 --> 05:13.271
♪♪

05:13.271 --> 05:15.899
[ Insects chirping ]

05:15.899 --> 05:18.235
[ Rooster crows ]

05:18.235 --> 05:25.867
♪♪

05:25.867 --> 05:28.662
♪♪

05:28.662 --> 05:30.622
[ Brakes squeal ]

05:30.622 --> 05:33.500
♪♪

05:33.500 --> 05:41.341
♪♪

05:41.341 --> 05:44.010
Hello, I'm Dr. Mateo Rendón.

05:44.010 --> 05:46.346
Dr. Saravia and her team
have spent several months

05:46.346 --> 05:47.806
gathering cases.

05:47.806 --> 05:49.432
From those, we selected 40.

05:49.432 --> 05:51.059
You're going to want
to save them all.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.102
You will not.

05:52.102 --> 05:53.895
We will perform
12 operations.

05:53.895 --> 05:56.064
I'm Dr. Marcus Andrews,
last‐minute addition.

05:56.064 --> 05:57.315
If we could add more cases,
I ‐‐

05:57.315 --> 05:58.275
Before I heard
you joined the trip,

05:58.275 --> 06:00.193
we were doing 10 surgeries.

06:00.193 --> 06:03.405
My organization has spent years
building trust.

06:03.405 --> 06:06.700
We save 12 people here,
that trust grows,

06:06.700 --> 06:10.120
more patients come to us,
more doctors volunteer.

06:10.120 --> 06:12.122
But if we lose a patient...

06:15.041 --> 06:17.836
We want surgeries we can do
but the locals couldn't.

06:17.836 --> 06:21.047
Surgeries that don't need
a lot of aftercare.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.592
12 patients, one alternate.

06:23.592 --> 06:26.219
Everyone else gets sent home,

06:26.219 --> 06:30.724
no matter how sick they are
or how sad their story is.

06:30.724 --> 06:33.685
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:33.685 --> 06:42.027
♪♪

06:42.027 --> 06:50.577
♪♪

06:50.577 --> 06:58.877
♪♪

06:58.877 --> 07:07.260
♪♪

07:13.141 --> 07:15.393
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:15.393 --> 07:17.771
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:17.771 --> 07:27.489
♪♪

07:27.489 --> 07:29.616
Uh, can you please tell me
what this means?

07:29.616 --> 07:30.700
Family...

07:30.700 --> 07:32.952
Your next of kin.

07:32.952 --> 07:34.496
Oh, well, nobody.

07:34.496 --> 07:35.997
Only Ignacio.

07:35.997 --> 07:37.248
Iggy is my only family.

07:37.248 --> 07:38.750
[ Dog whines ]

07:38.750 --> 07:41.836
He says his dog, Iggy.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.505
Ugly dog.

07:43.505 --> 07:45.548
Roberto Kantun Diaz?

07:45.548 --> 07:46.925
Yes!

07:46.925 --> 07:49.928
Andrea Torres Tzul?

07:49.928 --> 07:52.222
Aimé Navarro Gomez?

07:52.222 --> 07:54.224
♪♪

07:54.224 --> 07:55.558
Aimé Navarro Gomez?

07:55.558 --> 07:57.769
Here! Here!

07:57.769 --> 08:00.480
♪♪

08:00.480 --> 08:02.774
We need to do an abdominal exam
and ultrasound

08:02.774 --> 08:06.361
to see if there are any signs
of obstruction or strangulation.

08:06.361 --> 08:08.196
Please remove your bandage
and lie back.

08:08.196 --> 08:10.156
Lie down and remove
your bandages.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.792
How long
have you had that?

08:20.792 --> 08:23.628
A year...
Maybe more.

08:23.628 --> 08:25.547
He's had it for a year,
maybe longer.

08:25.547 --> 08:28.091
My neighbor told me to go
to the hospital in Xela...

08:28.091 --> 08:29.968
but I didn't have enough
for the trip...

08:29.968 --> 08:32.637
and I can't go a long time
without working.

08:32.637 --> 08:35.181
I'm the only one who takes care
of my sisters.

08:35.181 --> 08:36.599
He was told
to go to the hospital,

08:36.599 --> 08:38.935
but he couldn't afford the trip
or to miss work.

08:38.935 --> 08:41.646
He's the sole provider
for his siblings.

08:41.646 --> 08:45.108
Our parents died
two years ago.

08:45.108 --> 08:47.402
Their parents died
two years ago.

08:47.402 --> 08:51.573
♪♪

08:51.573 --> 08:56.119
She has a large
patent ductus arteriosus.

08:56.119 --> 08:58.872
I've only seen this condition
in infants.

08:58.872 --> 09:01.082
The blood is reversed.

09:01.082 --> 09:03.334
It's flowing the wrong way.

09:03.334 --> 09:04.836
[ Monitor beeps ]

09:07.088 --> 09:09.299
We could try going through
the femoral vein,

09:09.299 --> 09:11.634
do a percutaneous
device closure.

09:11.634 --> 09:15.638
She has irreversible
pulmonary hypertension.

09:15.638 --> 09:17.932
It would have been simple
to treat as an infant,

09:17.932 --> 09:23.646
but now closing the hole will ‐‐
will...kill her.

09:23.646 --> 09:27.859
♪♪

09:27.859 --> 09:30.987
Aimé's condition
is much too advanced.

09:32.947 --> 09:34.824
There's nothing we can do.

09:34.824 --> 09:35.867
[ Whimpers ]

09:35.867 --> 09:37.577
I'm sorry.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.746
[ Crying ]

09:39.746 --> 09:41.372
I'm sorry.

09:41.372 --> 09:42.832
No.

09:42.832 --> 09:46.419
[ Crying ] No.

09:46.419 --> 09:48.797
No, no.

09:48.797 --> 09:52.300
[ Crying ]

09:52.300 --> 09:59.516
♪♪

09:59.516 --> 10:01.893
[ Sighs ]

10:01.893 --> 10:03.770
Karla: Tissue?
Uh ‐‐

10:06.272 --> 10:09.609
I stock up
before the Americans come.

10:09.609 --> 10:10.860
And the French.

10:10.860 --> 10:13.988
They are surprisingly
sensitive people.

10:13.988 --> 10:16.241
I'm sorry. I know
this isn't helping anyone.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.409
[ Chuckles nervously ]
Never apologize for being human.

10:18.409 --> 10:20.745
I have a strict policy
against it.

10:22.288 --> 10:25.667
This week, you are
not just doing surgery.

10:25.667 --> 10:27.544
You are doing miracles.

10:27.544 --> 10:30.880
You're giving people hope
who had none.

10:30.880 --> 10:33.091
Except for the ones
that we send home to die.

10:33.091 --> 10:35.844
[ Sighs ]

10:35.844 --> 10:37.554
Focus on the miracles,

10:37.554 --> 10:40.265
or else you won't be able
to help any of them.

10:43.059 --> 10:44.519
And I will have to get
more tissues.

10:44.519 --> 10:47.313
[ Chuckles ]

10:47.313 --> 10:49.065
Thank you.

10:50.567 --> 10:52.443
[ Sniffles ]

10:55.864 --> 10:57.991
Bastion Alonso Ramos.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.909
12‐year‐old baseball fan.

10:59.909 --> 11:02.036
Roots for
the St. Louis Cardinals.

11:02.036 --> 11:04.038
Also, he has
an ameloblastoma.

11:04.038 --> 11:06.166
Not a lot of baseball fans
in Guatemala.

11:06.166 --> 11:09.836
You've been here before, or do
you enjoy reading Wikipedia?

11:09.836 --> 11:13.339
I did a medical mission here
during my residency.

11:13.339 --> 11:17.051
Oh, that explains
"Dr. Toilet Seat."

11:17.051 --> 11:19.053
You already
have a nickname.

11:19.053 --> 11:22.140
♪♪

11:22.140 --> 11:23.850
Good afternoon, Bastion.

11:23.850 --> 11:26.603
♪♪

11:26.603 --> 11:27.854
I'm Dr. Andrews.

11:27.854 --> 11:31.482
Good afternoon, Bastion.
This is Dr. Andrews.

11:31.482 --> 11:33.610
Hello, Dr. Andrews.

11:33.610 --> 11:36.237
Hello!

11:36.237 --> 11:38.531
What is that?
Let me see.

11:38.531 --> 11:41.451
♪♪

11:41.451 --> 11:43.369
[ Laughs ] Oh.

11:43.369 --> 11:45.205
That looks like Yadi Molina.

11:45.205 --> 11:46.748
Yes! It's Yadi Molina.

11:46.748 --> 11:48.416
St. Louis Cardinals.

11:48.416 --> 11:50.084
Mm‐hmm.

11:50.084 --> 11:52.170
So, are you a better
hitter or catcher?

11:52.170 --> 11:54.964
♪♪

11:57.550 --> 12:07.518
♪♪

12:07.518 --> 12:17.195
♪♪

12:17.195 --> 12:26.829
♪♪

12:26.829 --> 12:36.673
♪♪

12:36.673 --> 12:40.301
He has a hepatic adenoma
in the right lobe of his liver.

12:40.301 --> 12:41.552
Does not appear cancerous.

12:41.552 --> 12:44.097
No. For now.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.266
The lesion is localized,
well‐circumscribed,

12:46.266 --> 12:48.643
and not close
to portal vein branches.

12:48.643 --> 12:50.895
There's a tumor
in Adelmo's liver,

12:50.895 --> 12:52.647
but it's not cancer.

12:52.647 --> 12:55.191
The doctor believes
they can remove it.

12:55.191 --> 12:56.776
He's a good candidate.

12:56.776 --> 12:59.696
♪♪

12:59.696 --> 13:00.947
[ Chuckles ]

13:00.947 --> 13:06.244
♪♪

13:06.244 --> 13:07.745
Thank you.
Thank you.
Thank you.

13:07.745 --> 13:09.289
Cheers!
Cheers!
Cheers!

13:09.289 --> 13:11.499
[ Laughs ]

13:11.499 --> 13:14.043
I can continue like this
for a long time.

13:14.043 --> 13:15.503
But you have
a strange accent.

13:15.503 --> 13:19.215
It's not from Guatemala,
or Mexican.

13:19.215 --> 13:21.009
Did you spend some time
in Venezuela?

13:21.009 --> 13:23.303
In the library
where I grew up,

13:23.303 --> 13:27.390
they had some tapes named
"Speak Spanish like a Spaniard."

13:27.390 --> 13:29.726
I listened to them
every night

13:29.726 --> 13:32.186
until they broke.

13:32.186 --> 13:34.022
Oh, thank you. I thought you put
this kid in the "no" pile.

13:34.022 --> 13:35.940
I decided to take a closer look
at the images.

13:35.940 --> 13:37.734
See where the mass is thinning
the orbital floor

13:37.734 --> 13:39.527
and extending up
near the skull base?

13:39.527 --> 13:41.779
But that's exactly
what you can't do.

13:41.779 --> 13:45.491
Reconsider?
Weigh issues?

13:45.491 --> 13:47.118
Let emotional
and personal attachment

13:47.118 --> 13:49.370
influence
treatment decisions.

13:49.370 --> 13:50.580
Chicharrones?

13:50.580 --> 13:52.540
There's no beveling
or erosions.

13:52.540 --> 13:54.542
I can stay extracranial

13:54.542 --> 13:58.588
and create a bony plane
to resect the superior tumor.

13:58.588 --> 14:00.965
Did that sound
too emotional?

14:00.965 --> 14:03.176
Even if you stay
out of the brain,

14:03.176 --> 14:06.179
two major arteries are involved.
He could bleed out.

14:06.179 --> 14:09.640
[ Upbeat Spanish music
playing over speakers ]

14:09.640 --> 14:12.351
Can I get
one of those, please?

14:12.351 --> 14:14.020
[ Crunching ]

14:14.020 --> 14:15.438
♪♪

14:21.736 --> 14:23.946
[ Sheep bleating ]

14:23.946 --> 14:30.244
♪♪

14:30.244 --> 14:33.998
Apply it twice a day,
for 10 days.

14:35.917 --> 14:37.502
Thank you,
Dr. Shaun Murphy.

14:37.502 --> 14:39.045
Thank you.

14:39.045 --> 14:41.172
You're welcome.

14:41.172 --> 14:46.135
♪♪

14:46.135 --> 14:49.055
My chest hurts,
and so does my arm.

14:49.055 --> 14:51.099
And sometimes,
my hand feels cold,

14:51.099 --> 14:54.060
or it's as if I wasn't able
to feel it at all.

14:54.060 --> 14:56.687
It could be angina
or a blockage,

14:56.687 --> 14:58.773
which requires
bypass surgery.

14:58.773 --> 15:02.443
We should do an EKG before
he goes to the cath lab ‐‐

15:02.443 --> 15:05.696
You don't have a cath lab.

15:05.696 --> 15:07.573
Stretch out your arm,
please.

15:07.573 --> 15:09.534
Turn your head
to the side.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.079
Feel his pulse.

15:14.080 --> 15:16.749
♪♪

15:16.749 --> 15:18.417
There isn't one.

15:18.417 --> 15:20.920
Turn your head
forward.

15:20.920 --> 15:24.674
♪♪

15:24.674 --> 15:26.843
His pulse is back.

15:28.761 --> 15:31.347
It's not
a cardiac problem.

15:31.347 --> 15:33.558
He has thoracic
outlet syndrome.

15:33.558 --> 15:36.644
Dr. Saravia has just showed me
that the nerves and arteries

15:36.644 --> 15:39.063
in your neck and chest are being
compressed by your ribs.

15:39.063 --> 15:40.731
It's a very rare condition,

15:40.731 --> 15:45.194
that may cause blood clots
or an embolism ‐‐

15:45.194 --> 15:48.489
He doesn't seem happy.

15:48.489 --> 15:49.782
Did I translate wrong?

15:49.782 --> 15:52.368
No.
Your Spanish is perfect.

15:52.368 --> 15:55.496
But you left out
that his problem can be fixed.

15:56.873 --> 15:57.957
It can be remedied.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.667
Oh, okay.

16:00.918 --> 16:03.087
Okay.

16:03.087 --> 16:05.840
I am not good
at communication.

16:05.840 --> 16:07.633
In two languages.

16:07.633 --> 16:10.303
♪♪

16:10.303 --> 16:16.142
The nurse should
come momentarily.

16:18.186 --> 16:20.313
The translator
should be here soon.

16:20.313 --> 16:22.732
Um ‐‐
If you want, I can translate.

16:22.732 --> 16:24.108
Oh, you can speak English?

16:24.108 --> 16:25.902
We lived in the U. S.
for a few years.

16:25.902 --> 16:27.904
Uh, my mother
cleaned houses.

16:27.904 --> 16:29.197
I watched "Grey's Anatomy."

16:29.197 --> 16:30.448
[ Laughs ] Oh.

16:30.448 --> 16:34.660
Well, being a surgeon
is not much like that.

16:34.660 --> 16:38.206
Ms. Garza, can you show me
where you feel pain?

16:39.498 --> 16:41.959
Show them where
it hurts you, Mom.

16:42.919 --> 16:44.420
Here.

16:44.420 --> 16:47.673
And do you have indigestion
or cramping

16:47.673 --> 16:50.593
or ever feel like
you might throw up?

16:50.593 --> 16:53.387
She wants to know if you have
indigestion or cramping.

16:53.387 --> 16:55.056
Do you feel like you
might throw up?

16:57.183 --> 16:59.143
Sometimes.

16:59.143 --> 17:01.229
"Sometimes."

17:01.229 --> 17:03.981
But she's lying.
It's always.

17:05.691 --> 17:08.653
She has fevers, too,
and throws up.

17:11.239 --> 17:14.116
I need to feel your abdomen.
Can you lie on the bed for me?

17:14.116 --> 17:15.785
She has to feel
your stomach, Mom.

17:15.785 --> 17:17.161
Lie down.

17:19.747 --> 17:21.540
Okay.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.503
Mm.

17:25.503 --> 17:27.505
[ Grunts ]

17:27.505 --> 17:31.259
Ms. Garza, I think
you have gallstones.

17:31.259 --> 17:33.135
We will have to run some tests,

17:33.135 --> 17:35.972
but it is likely
that you will need surgery.

17:38.599 --> 17:42.270
Mom, the doctor believes
you have gallstones.

17:42.270 --> 17:44.855
They need to do a test
to be sure,

17:44.855 --> 17:48.943
but you need surgery.

17:48.943 --> 17:51.737
No, no.
Not surgery.

17:51.737 --> 17:54.490
I came here for medicine.

17:54.490 --> 17:56.284
You told me they were gonna
give me medicine.

17:56.284 --> 17:57.994
Don't be stubborn.
Do what the doctor says.

17:59.912 --> 18:03.666
If she doesn't want surgery,
why is she here?

18:03.666 --> 18:07.378
I told her you would have pills
that would help her.

18:07.378 --> 18:09.922
I told her I wouldn't eat
until she came.

18:09.922 --> 18:11.924
♪♪

18:11.924 --> 18:14.885
I have to work.

18:14.885 --> 18:16.220
I need to take care of you.

18:16.220 --> 18:18.306
She says
she can't miss work.

18:18.306 --> 18:20.683
She needs
to take care of me.

18:20.683 --> 18:24.312
♪♪

18:24.312 --> 18:27.398
I‐I need you to translate
accurately.

18:27.398 --> 18:29.609
♪♪

18:29.609 --> 18:33.154
My mother was very sick, too.

18:33.154 --> 18:36.282
Her mother
also was very sick.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.659
And she tried
to hide her pain,

18:38.659 --> 18:41.662
but children know
when people are suffering ‐‐

18:41.662 --> 18:45.291
especially their mothers.

18:45.291 --> 18:47.126
She tried to hide her pain,

18:47.126 --> 18:51.547
but kids know when people
are suffering.

18:51.547 --> 18:54.050
Especially
when it's their mother.

18:56.260 --> 18:58.804
You can't take care
of your daughter

18:58.804 --> 19:01.182
if you do not
take care of yourself.

19:03.392 --> 19:05.561
You can't take care
of your daughter

19:05.561 --> 19:07.855
if you don't take care
of yourself.

19:07.855 --> 19:10.775
♪♪

19:10.775 --> 19:12.860
[ Sighs ]

19:12.860 --> 19:19.325
♪♪

19:19.325 --> 19:20.576
Andrews:
Did you review Bastion's file?

19:20.576 --> 19:22.203
Doing a bifrontal trepanation

19:22.203 --> 19:23.579
and reconstructing
the skull base

19:23.579 --> 19:25.414
could prevent
brain herniation.

19:25.414 --> 19:27.333
What about risk
of CSF leak?

19:27.333 --> 19:29.126
It reduces with
a multilayer duraplasty

19:29.126 --> 19:31.337
using a pericranial flap.

19:31.337 --> 19:33.506
Lim: I say five sentences
to a patient.

19:33.506 --> 19:34.840
You say five words.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.384
A nurse wanted me
to give this to you.

19:36.384 --> 19:37.760
Because medical jargon
does nothing

19:37.760 --> 19:39.804
but scare them
and waste our time.

19:39.804 --> 19:41.597
All they care about is,
can we help ‐‐

19:41.597 --> 19:42.807
yes or no?

19:42.807 --> 19:46.143
♪♪

19:46.143 --> 19:48.145
[ Sighs ]

19:48.145 --> 19:56.195
♪♪

19:56.195 --> 20:04.412
♪♪

20:04.412 --> 20:07.373
Morgan: Your son's heart valves
are damaged.

20:07.373 --> 20:10.918
Your son's heart valves
are damaged.

20:10.918 --> 20:13.713
It's probably the result of
his rheumatic fever last year.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.798
Probably as a result

20:15.798 --> 20:19.301
of the rheumatic fever
he had last year.

20:19.301 --> 20:21.637
Because of his heart,

20:21.637 --> 20:24.056
we can't remove
his liver tumor.

20:25.558 --> 20:28.018
I‐It makes the surgery
too risky.

20:29.603 --> 20:31.647
I'm very sorry.

20:31.647 --> 20:34.525
♪♪

20:34.525 --> 20:39.280
Due to his heart, we can't
remove the tumor in his liver

20:39.280 --> 20:43.701
because it makes the surgery
very risky.

20:43.701 --> 20:45.786
We are very sorry.

20:45.786 --> 20:54.295
♪♪

20:54.295 --> 20:55.963
Thank you, Doctor.

20:57.882 --> 20:59.425
Uh, no, I'm sorry.

20:59.425 --> 21:02.219
W‐We can't do the operation
on your son.

21:02.219 --> 21:04.263
He ‐‐ I'm not sure he ‐‐

21:04.263 --> 21:06.140
But you tried.

21:06.140 --> 21:08.100
♪♪

21:08.100 --> 21:10.519
Thank you for trying.

21:10.519 --> 21:12.730
God bless you.

21:12.730 --> 21:18.652
♪♪

21:18.652 --> 21:24.241
♪♪

21:24.241 --> 21:26.410
Everything's gonna be okay.

21:26.410 --> 21:28.537
Don't worry.

21:28.537 --> 21:34.627
♪♪

21:34.627 --> 21:40.257
♪♪

21:45.095 --> 21:47.932
León Castillo. 22‐year‐old male.

21:47.932 --> 21:50.267
Large, non‐reducible
umbilical hernia.

21:50.267 --> 21:52.269
He's the sole provider
for his siblings ‐‐

21:52.269 --> 21:54.396
No personal details.
They're irrelevant.

21:54.396 --> 21:56.315
Two children's survival
depends on his.

21:56.315 --> 21:57.483
Seems relevant to me.

21:57.483 --> 22:00.569
Decisions need to be based
on medical data alone.

22:00.569 --> 22:03.614
This can't turn into a contest
of whose life is more tragic.

22:03.614 --> 22:05.074
There would be
too many winners.

22:08.619 --> 22:10.329
Without surgery,

22:10.329 --> 22:13.374
the hernia's at a very high risk
for strangulation.

22:13.374 --> 22:15.042
It's a fast, simple procedure,

22:15.042 --> 22:17.169
and he will almost certainly
have a full recovery.

22:17.169 --> 22:21.882
From a surgery he could survive
another 15 years without.

22:21.882 --> 22:23.884
Replacing the valve
with a bioprosthetic

22:23.884 --> 22:26.262
means he won't need
to be on blood thinners forever.

22:26.262 --> 22:27.888
Morgan: But he'll probably need
follow‐up surgeries

22:27.888 --> 22:29.431
to replace the replacement.

22:29.431 --> 22:31.809
Well, this guy's an athlete,
a fútbol star.

22:31.809 --> 22:33.686
Is that relevant?

22:33.686 --> 22:35.729
♪♪

22:35.729 --> 22:38.357
Yes, because his underlying
cardiac health is excellent.

22:38.357 --> 22:40.025
He should make
a full recovery.

22:40.025 --> 22:42.319
Unfortunately,
his dental health isn't.

22:42.319 --> 22:45.447
He has cavities, which puts him
at high risk for endocarditis,

22:45.447 --> 22:47.616
which would contribute
to valve deterioration.

22:47.616 --> 22:49.910
A total abdominal colectomy

22:49.910 --> 22:53.205
offers her an 80% to 90% chance
at full recovery.

22:53.205 --> 22:55.958
Otherwise healthy,
no complicating factors.

22:55.958 --> 22:58.794
The tumor could be removed
using ultrasound‐guided surgery.

22:58.794 --> 23:01.088
But she has no access
to post‐op chemo and radiation.

23:01.088 --> 23:03.007
The mass is round, localized.

23:03.007 --> 23:05.384
No signs of infiltration
in the adjacent structures.

23:05.384 --> 23:06.844
Minimal chance of recurrence.

23:06.844 --> 23:08.470
If you get all of it.

23:08.470 --> 23:11.348
♪♪

23:11.348 --> 23:12.516
She just got married
last week...

23:12.516 --> 23:14.101
Dr. Reznick.

23:14.101 --> 23:16.353
...which is medically relevant,
because studies have shown

23:16.353 --> 23:18.772
optimistic people
have better long‐term prognosis.

23:18.772 --> 23:20.649
And she is full of hope.

23:20.649 --> 23:28.616
♪♪

23:28.616 --> 23:30.409
Uh, there's a boy.

23:30.409 --> 23:31.869
He needs blankets. Uh.

23:31.869 --> 23:33.245
Blankets, please?

23:33.245 --> 23:34.496
There.

23:34.496 --> 23:35.915
Thank you.

23:35.915 --> 23:37.958
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:43.631 --> 23:45.466
[ Baby fussing ]

23:47.343 --> 23:53.474
♪♪

23:53.474 --> 23:59.647
♪♪

23:59.647 --> 24:01.690
[ Sighs ]

24:01.690 --> 24:04.443
♪♪

24:04.443 --> 24:05.653
Claire: The gallstones

24:05.653 --> 24:07.655
are intermittently
blocking the bile duct,

24:07.655 --> 24:10.491
which could lead to ascending
cholangitis, sepsis, and death.

24:10.491 --> 24:12.534
Her condition
might respond to medication.

24:12.534 --> 24:13.744
No, it's extremely unlikely

24:13.744 --> 24:15.287
given how advanced
her symptoms are.

24:15.287 --> 24:17.498
But she has
a non‐surgical option.

24:17.498 --> 24:18.832
Bastion doesn't.

24:18.832 --> 24:20.376
It's a miracle
he made it to 12.

24:20.376 --> 24:22.628
Without surgery,
he will not see 15.

24:22.628 --> 24:24.296
He's unable
to eat solid foods.

24:24.296 --> 24:26.090
He's already showing
signs of malnutrition.

24:26.090 --> 24:28.467
Shaun's surgical plan
is very ambitious.

24:28.467 --> 24:31.220
It runs the risk
of graft failure and necrosis.

24:31.220 --> 24:32.972
You could leave this boy
worse off.

24:32.972 --> 24:35.391
Meanwhile, Edna's surgery
is straightforward,

24:35.391 --> 24:38.310
and she is all
her daughter has in the world.

24:38.310 --> 24:39.687
Who a person is

24:39.687 --> 24:42.356
cannot be completely separated
from their medical care.

24:42.356 --> 24:44.566
And I'm done
pretending it can be.

24:44.566 --> 24:47.361
♪♪

24:47.361 --> 24:49.113
[ Sighs ]

24:50.948 --> 24:52.908
We've got a mom
who needs a simple procedure

24:52.908 --> 24:56.161
she might live without...

24:56.161 --> 25:00.499
or a son whose only shot at life
is a very complicated surgery

25:00.499 --> 25:02.584
that may not work.

25:02.584 --> 25:09.466
♪♪

25:09.466 --> 25:16.640
♪♪

25:16.640 --> 25:23.772
♪♪

25:23.772 --> 25:26.650
[ All gasp, chuckle ]

25:26.650 --> 25:32.239
♪♪

25:32.239 --> 25:34.742
We have to focus
on the miracles.

25:34.742 --> 25:38.454
[ Sighs ]

25:38.454 --> 25:40.414
Let's go eat.

25:40.414 --> 25:44.460
♪♪

25:44.460 --> 25:46.462
Okay, so,
look at the nail bed.

25:46.462 --> 25:48.797
Karla said if you see
alternating redness

25:48.797 --> 25:52.634
with the pulse, that's a sign
of aortic insufficiency.

25:52.634 --> 25:55.554
So, your heart is fine,
and your cuticles are great.

25:55.554 --> 25:57.723
I get manicures.

25:57.723 --> 26:00.684
[ Upbeat Spanish music
playing over speakers ]

26:00.684 --> 26:02.811
Ah, you like?

26:02.811 --> 26:05.147
It's a national treasure.

26:05.147 --> 26:08.984
No. I just wanted
the experience.

26:08.984 --> 26:11.403
I shouldn't have any more.
First day of surgery tomorrow.

26:11.403 --> 26:13.530
Oh, no, I'm good.
Mm.

26:13.530 --> 26:17.409
♪♪

26:17.409 --> 26:19.953
[ Ana laughs ]

26:19.953 --> 26:21.997
Ah.
[ Both laugh ]

26:21.997 --> 26:23.499
You are terrible
at this!

26:23.499 --> 26:25.626
I am terrible,
but I look fantastic.

26:25.626 --> 26:27.419
Watch this.

26:27.419 --> 26:29.046
[ Laughs ]
I'll get us another round.

26:29.046 --> 26:30.798
[ Laughs ] Okay.

26:30.798 --> 26:32.883
Tequila, two, please.

26:32.883 --> 26:35.135
Mm.

26:35.135 --> 26:38.097
What's going on
over there?

26:38.097 --> 26:40.599
Uh, I'm getting
my ass kicked in darts.

26:40.599 --> 26:42.768
You're flirting.

26:42.768 --> 26:44.436
Just being nice.

26:44.436 --> 26:47.147
Well, don't be so nice that you
regret it when you get home.

26:47.147 --> 26:50.275
♪♪

26:50.275 --> 26:52.820
You have nothing
to worry about.

26:52.820 --> 26:55.489
I guarantee it.

26:55.489 --> 26:57.449
Alright, I'm gonna grab a cab
back to the hotel.

26:57.449 --> 26:59.243
Okay.

26:59.243 --> 27:03.163
♪♪

27:03.163 --> 27:04.623
Up, down, to the center
and to the belly.

27:04.623 --> 27:07.126
Lim: Good night, guys.

27:07.126 --> 27:11.296
♪♪

27:11.296 --> 27:14.049
[ Insects chirping ]

27:14.049 --> 27:17.511
Uh, Hotel Provincia?

27:17.511 --> 27:19.179
Yeah.

27:21.765 --> 27:23.141
Mind if I tag along?

27:23.141 --> 27:25.185
Big day tomorrow.
Sure.

27:25.185 --> 27:27.145
[ Engine starts ]

27:33.735 --> 27:36.071
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:36.071 --> 27:40.158
♪♪

27:40.158 --> 27:42.035
I saw you break the news
to that boy's dad.

27:42.035 --> 27:44.037
♪♪

27:44.037 --> 27:46.331
You want
to talk about it?

27:46.331 --> 27:55.507
♪♪

27:55.507 --> 27:56.925
Morgan.

27:59.344 --> 28:02.014
I just wanted to know
if you're okay.

28:02.014 --> 28:03.181
You don't get
to ask me that anymore.

28:03.181 --> 28:05.726
We're not friends.

28:05.726 --> 28:07.060
You drew a line.

28:07.060 --> 28:09.271
So don't ask me how I am

28:09.271 --> 28:10.898
and then pretend to be
some nice guy who cares,

28:10.898 --> 28:12.524
when you obviously don't.

28:12.524 --> 28:19.656
♪♪

28:19.656 --> 28:22.618
I‐I just got a text from Karla.
Miguel is crashing.

28:22.618 --> 28:24.578
Shaun and I are gonna head back
to the hospital.

28:24.578 --> 28:29.708
♪♪

28:29.708 --> 28:34.838
♪♪

28:36.840 --> 28:37.799
[ Horn honks in distance ]

28:37.799 --> 28:39.843
[ Sighs ] Eight?

28:39.843 --> 28:42.471
I'm only fluent in six.

28:42.471 --> 28:44.097
[ Chuckles ]
I didn't set out to learn them.

28:44.097 --> 28:46.391
I just picked them up
as I moved around.

28:46.391 --> 28:49.728
Oh, so you're an accidental
language genius?

28:49.728 --> 28:51.188
[ Both chuckle ]

28:54.816 --> 28:56.860
So, what are
some of these places,

28:56.860 --> 28:58.487
I mean, that you
moved around to?

28:58.487 --> 29:00.030
Uh, I was born in Mexico.

29:00.030 --> 29:02.699
Went to medical school
in New Haven.

29:02.699 --> 29:04.242
Did my residency
in Chicago.

29:04.242 --> 29:07.663
Stayed a while in Syria,
Haiti, the Congo.

29:07.663 --> 29:10.374
You throw in your stop
at Yale to impress me?

29:10.374 --> 29:13.085
I threw in my stop at the Congo
to impress you.

29:13.085 --> 29:14.711
[ Chuckles ]

29:20.968 --> 29:22.844
Hey, this is not the way
to the Provincia Hotel.

29:22.844 --> 29:24.638
Where are you taking us?

29:24.638 --> 29:27.224
We're gonna make a stop.

29:27.224 --> 29:28.809
Do you want money?

29:28.809 --> 29:31.228
I don't need your money.

29:31.228 --> 29:34.856
♪♪

29:34.856 --> 29:37.567
What's happening?

29:37.567 --> 29:40.487
Don't be too alarmed,
but we're being kidnapped.

29:40.487 --> 29:45.075
♪♪

29:50.789 --> 29:52.416
[ Frogs croaking ]

29:52.416 --> 29:57.879
♪♪

29:57.879 --> 30:06.555
♪♪

30:06.555 --> 30:08.056
[ Engine shuts off ]

30:09.975 --> 30:12.769
Come in, please!
Hurry!

30:12.769 --> 30:17.899
♪♪

30:17.899 --> 30:19.109
This is my niece.

30:19.109 --> 30:21.111
She's been in labor
for 14 hours.

30:21.111 --> 30:24.072
Mateo: 14 hours like this.

30:24.072 --> 30:26.491
Hello. I'm a doctor.

30:26.491 --> 30:28.452
Uh, can you handle
the additional talking?

30:28.452 --> 30:30.245
We're here to help you
and your baby, okay?

30:30.245 --> 30:31.747
We're going to examine you,
yeah?

30:31.747 --> 30:32.873
It hurts so bad!

30:32.873 --> 30:35.667
Yes, here we go.

30:35.667 --> 30:38.211
Well, the baby's head is down,
so position's not a problem.

30:38.211 --> 30:40.130
[ Panting ]

30:43.592 --> 30:44.843
I can't hear anything.

30:47.054 --> 30:49.431
The cab driver, he had a‐a‐a cup
of coffee in his cab.

30:49.431 --> 30:50.974
Have him get it.

30:50.974 --> 30:52.809
Um, a cup of coffee
from the taxi...

30:52.809 --> 30:55.812
Go get it quickly!

30:55.812 --> 30:57.439
Please tell her
I have to check her cervix.

30:57.439 --> 30:59.316
The doctor will check
your cervix.

30:59.316 --> 31:01.401
Okay,
yes, that's fine.

31:01.401 --> 31:04.529
[ Whimpering, panting ]

31:04.529 --> 31:06.531
She's fully dilated.

31:06.531 --> 31:08.909
♪♪

31:08.909 --> 31:11.119
Okay, tear out the bottom,
hand it to me.

31:11.119 --> 31:17.417
♪♪

31:17.417 --> 31:19.711
I can hear a heartbeat.

31:19.711 --> 31:21.463
The baby has decels.

31:21.463 --> 31:22.798
[ Whimpers, groans ]

31:22.798 --> 31:24.758
Oh, no, no! Don't push!
Don't push!

31:24.758 --> 31:26.510
[ Whimpers ]

31:26.510 --> 31:29.221
He became short of breath
and then lost consciousness.

31:29.221 --> 31:31.348
I believe his
thoracic outlet syndrome

31:31.348 --> 31:34.601
caused a clot in his arm,
which went into his lungs.

31:34.601 --> 31:36.103
That would explain
the drop in blood pressure

31:36.103 --> 31:37.312
and respiratory rate.

31:37.312 --> 31:40.065
But not his elevated
end tidal CO2 level.

31:40.065 --> 31:43.568
That is inconsistent
with a pulmonary embolism.

31:43.568 --> 31:45.737
♪♪

31:45.737 --> 31:47.697
What is it
consistent with, Shaun?

31:47.697 --> 31:54.579
♪♪

31:54.579 --> 32:01.753
♪♪

32:01.753 --> 32:04.673
His brain. A clot
that traveled from his arm

32:04.673 --> 32:06.174
through a hole in his heart
into his aorta

32:06.174 --> 32:07.676
and up to his brain.

32:07.676 --> 32:13.431
♪♪

32:13.431 --> 32:14.975
[ Gags ]

32:14.975 --> 32:18.145
His gag reflex is only active
on one side.

32:18.145 --> 32:20.689
I was right. He has a small clot
in the brain stem

32:20.689 --> 32:23.316
near the respiratory center.

32:23.316 --> 32:25.110
Well, we can surgically remove
a clot in his lung,

32:25.110 --> 32:27.237
but in his brain...

32:27.237 --> 32:28.613
We can't do that here.

32:28.613 --> 32:32.409
If we have TPA,
we could break it up.

32:32.409 --> 32:34.744
TPA? No.

32:34.744 --> 32:38.832
But we have
a snake venom derivative.

32:38.832 --> 32:41.126
I‐It does the same thing,
more or less.

32:41.126 --> 32:45.672
♪♪

32:45.672 --> 32:47.924
Mateo: Any movement at all?
None.

32:47.924 --> 32:49.134
No cord presentation.

32:49.134 --> 32:50.927
Maybe her pelvis
is too narrow?

32:50.927 --> 32:52.095
The heart rate's
getting slower.

32:52.095 --> 32:53.722
[ Groans ]
Wait, wait, wait.

32:53.722 --> 32:54.598
I can feel a hand
by the face.

32:54.598 --> 32:56.391
[ Groaning ]

32:56.391 --> 32:59.394
The baby's sucking its thumb.
That's why it's not progressing.

32:59.394 --> 33:01.521
I can do an episiotomy,
try to pull the baby out,

33:01.521 --> 33:03.565
but with the arm where it's at,
I'm probably gonna

33:03.565 --> 33:07.068
break the clavicle and damage
the brachial plexus nerve.

33:07.068 --> 33:08.570
Reach inside...
Yeah.

33:08.570 --> 33:10.864
...find the baby's finger,
and pinch it hard.

33:10.864 --> 33:16.661
♪♪

33:16.661 --> 33:22.709
♪♪

33:22.709 --> 33:25.420
It worked.
[ Chuckles ]

33:25.420 --> 33:29.132
Okay, dear,
now we are going to push, okay?

33:29.132 --> 33:30.342
Push.
Push.

33:30.342 --> 33:32.636
[ Straining ]

33:32.636 --> 33:34.262
♪♪

33:34.262 --> 33:38.058
[ Baby cooing ]

33:38.058 --> 33:44.648
♪♪

33:44.648 --> 33:47.442
I'm sorry...

33:47.442 --> 33:49.486
Um...

33:49.486 --> 33:51.696
Do you speak English?

33:51.696 --> 33:54.074
No.
I don't speak English.

33:54.074 --> 33:56.034
♪♪

33:56.034 --> 33:58.578
My name is Lea...

33:58.578 --> 34:01.498
I'm with the Americans.

34:01.498 --> 34:02.749
Mm.

34:02.749 --> 34:04.918
I'm Sofía.

34:04.918 --> 34:08.755
He is my husband, Oscar.

34:08.755 --> 34:12.217
And she is Isabela.

34:12.217 --> 34:15.553
[ Chuckles ]

34:15.553 --> 34:18.348
Isabela.

34:18.348 --> 34:19.432
She is...

34:19.432 --> 34:21.351
perfect.

34:21.351 --> 34:24.729
[ Baby cooing ]

34:24.729 --> 34:26.773
Um...

34:26.773 --> 34:31.027
♪♪

34:31.027 --> 34:33.697
I found these
in my suitcase.

34:33.697 --> 34:35.824
My mom got them for ‐‐

34:35.824 --> 34:37.742
♪♪

34:37.742 --> 34:39.286
It gets cold in here.

34:39.286 --> 34:41.871
A gift for Isabela.

34:41.871 --> 34:43.581
[ Chuckles ]

34:43.581 --> 34:45.709
♪♪

34:45.709 --> 34:47.836
Thank you.

34:47.836 --> 34:50.797
♪♪

34:50.797 --> 34:53.675
Would you like
to hold her?

34:53.675 --> 35:02.392
♪♪

35:02.392 --> 35:03.768
Uh.

35:03.768 --> 35:05.770
No, thank you.

35:05.770 --> 35:08.023
Uh, I have to go.

35:08.023 --> 35:10.275
♪♪

35:10.275 --> 35:12.152
[ Sighs ]

35:12.152 --> 35:20.827
♪♪

35:20.827 --> 35:23.288
[ Baby crying ]

35:23.288 --> 35:25.123
♪♪

35:25.123 --> 35:28.793
Congratulations, Mom.

35:28.793 --> 35:31.004
What a good‐looking boy!

35:31.004 --> 35:40.096
♪♪

35:45.477 --> 35:50.148
♪♪

35:50.148 --> 35:53.401
Shaun's keeping an eye
on Miguel.

35:53.401 --> 35:56.363
Yeah.

35:56.363 --> 35:58.239
[ Sighs ]

35:58.239 --> 36:06.331
♪♪

36:06.331 --> 36:09.834
You know, it's okay
to not be okay.

36:09.834 --> 36:12.295
♪♪

36:12.295 --> 36:14.339
I j‐‐

36:14.339 --> 36:17.717
Every time I feel like
things are getting better...

36:17.717 --> 36:19.511
it's there again.

36:19.511 --> 36:21.721
♪♪

36:21.721 --> 36:24.683
Yeah, I know.

36:24.683 --> 36:26.643
Like it comes in waves.

36:28.353 --> 36:31.856
Eventually, it subsides.

36:31.856 --> 36:34.401
It's a process.

36:34.401 --> 36:36.986
It's a terrible process.

36:38.655 --> 36:41.449
And it's one you don't
have to go through alone.

36:41.449 --> 36:45.704
♪♪

36:45.704 --> 36:48.415
Shaun has no idea,
does he?

36:48.415 --> 36:50.166
No.

36:50.166 --> 36:54.295
♪♪

36:54.295 --> 36:56.423
He's doing great,
important work.

36:56.423 --> 36:59.467
I don't want
to interfere with that.

36:59.467 --> 37:02.971
And...

37:02.971 --> 37:06.391
he can't fix it.

37:06.391 --> 37:09.436
It's not about fixing it.

37:09.436 --> 37:13.690
It's about the two of you
just being in this together.

37:13.690 --> 37:18.445
♪♪

37:18.445 --> 37:21.197
[ Sighs ]

37:21.197 --> 37:23.241
Karla: He's waking up.

37:25.034 --> 37:27.871
What happened?

37:27.871 --> 37:29.998
You had an embolism,

37:29.998 --> 37:34.377
but we were able
to give you treatment.

37:34.377 --> 37:38.339
Can I still have
the operation tomorrow?

37:38.339 --> 37:40.091
[ FINNEAS' "What They'll
Say About Us" plays ]

37:40.091 --> 37:43.344
No, I'm afraid not.

37:45.096 --> 37:46.931
Tiziana?

37:46.931 --> 37:48.516
Tiziana, wake up.
♪ You're tired now, lie down ♪

37:48.516 --> 37:51.519
Hey, I need you
to tell your mother something.

37:51.519 --> 37:54.731
We're gonna do her surgery.

37:54.731 --> 37:57.901
Mom, Mom, they're going to do
your operation!

37:57.901 --> 38:00.153
[ Laughs ]
♪ It might take patience ♪

38:00.153 --> 38:02.530
♪ And when you wake up ♪

38:02.530 --> 38:07.076
You told me that I could die
without that surgery.

38:07.076 --> 38:11.539
♪ So don't you give up ♪

38:11.539 --> 38:13.583
♪ We've got the time ♪

38:13.583 --> 38:14.584
[ Both laugh ]

38:14.584 --> 38:17.378
♪ To take the world ♪

38:17.378 --> 38:18.880
Thank you!

38:18.880 --> 38:20.548
You're welcome.

38:20.548 --> 38:27.555
♪ And make it better
than it ever was ♪

38:27.555 --> 38:29.849
[ Insects chirping ]

38:29.849 --> 38:31.726
[ Dog whines ]

38:31.726 --> 38:34.938
♪♪

38:34.938 --> 38:37.690
[ Sighs ] That was...

38:37.690 --> 38:39.734
It was.

38:39.734 --> 38:47.325
♪♪

38:47.325 --> 38:48.993
Good night, Audrey Lim.

38:48.993 --> 38:55.583
♪♪

38:55.583 --> 38:57.043
You know...

38:57.043 --> 38:59.796
♪♪

38:59.796 --> 39:02.507
I'm...not really tired.

39:02.507 --> 39:07.011
♪♪

39:07.011 --> 39:08.847
Me either.

39:08.847 --> 39:17.522
♪♪

39:17.522 --> 39:21.025
Tomorrow, I will be removing
an adenocarcinoma

39:21.025 --> 39:23.486
from a young woman's
mediastinum.

39:23.486 --> 39:27.031
[ Spits ] That can be
a very dangerous area

39:27.031 --> 39:28.199
because of the vasculature.

39:31.619 --> 39:33.788
It will be
an excellent challenge.

39:34.998 --> 39:37.083
Are you coming to bed?

39:37.083 --> 39:38.710
I would like
to turn off the light.

39:44.007 --> 39:47.093
I don't want
to ruin your trip.

39:48.803 --> 39:50.471
You're having
such a good time.

39:50.471 --> 39:52.432
But...

39:52.432 --> 39:54.058
I'm not.

39:54.058 --> 39:55.435
W‐What's wrong?

39:55.435 --> 39:57.228
Are you sick?

39:57.228 --> 39:58.771
Did you open your mouth
in the shower?

39:58.771 --> 40:00.398
That is very common.

40:01.983 --> 40:06.029
I'm just...sad.

40:06.029 --> 40:07.906
Every time something reminds me
of the baby,

40:07.906 --> 40:09.407
I get even sadder.

40:09.407 --> 40:12.493
I'm glad you're doing
better than I am.

40:12.493 --> 40:14.746
I'm glad you're happy,
but...

40:14.746 --> 40:18.249
sometimes, you being happy
makes me feel worse.

40:20.001 --> 40:21.794
I hate
that I feel that way,

40:21.794 --> 40:23.171
and I didn't even want
to tell you,

40:23.171 --> 40:26.299
but I think
I need to tell you.

40:26.299 --> 40:27.800
I'm sorry.

40:29.218 --> 40:33.139
Do you want me
to not talk about work?

40:33.139 --> 40:35.642
No. I can't
ask you to do that.

40:35.642 --> 40:36.976
Yes, you can.

40:36.976 --> 40:38.770
I want you
to feel better.

40:38.770 --> 40:41.397
It won't help, Shaun.

40:41.397 --> 40:44.025
What will help?

40:45.485 --> 40:48.196
[ Sighs ]

40:48.196 --> 40:49.822
Nothing.

40:49.822 --> 40:53.284
♪♪

40:53.284 --> 40:55.244
I miss her so much.

40:56.996 --> 41:00.375
I mean, even looking at your
blue eyes breaks my heart,

41:00.375 --> 41:02.669
because I dreamed
she would have them.

41:02.669 --> 41:06.965
♪♪

41:06.965 --> 41:08.925
[ Sniffles ]

41:08.925 --> 41:12.845
[ Sighs ] My parents
are really worried,

41:12.845 --> 41:16.140
been calling all the time.

41:16.140 --> 41:20.144
They want me to come back
to Hershey for a while.

41:20.144 --> 41:22.480
They think it'll help.

41:22.480 --> 41:25.566
♪♪

41:25.566 --> 41:29.988
Do you...want to?

41:29.988 --> 41:33.491
♪♪

41:33.491 --> 41:37.996
I think it would be good for me
to get some time away.

41:37.996 --> 41:40.623
From everything.

41:40.623 --> 41:50.216
♪♪

41:50.216 --> 41:52.927
I'm sorry you're sad.

41:52.927 --> 42:01.227
♪♪

42:01.227 --> 42:09.527
♪♪

42:09.527 --> 42:11.279
♪♪

42:11.279 --> 42:13.489
[ Sighs ]

42:13.489 --> 42:17.493
♪♪
